function createUrgencyTimer() {
let deadline = new Date().getTime() + 900000; // 15 minutes from now

let countdown = setInterval(function() {
    let timeLeft = deadline - new Date().getTime();
    let seconds = Math.floor((timeLeft % (1000 * 60)) / 1000);
    let minutes = Math.floor((timeLeft % (1000 * 60 * 60)) / (1000 * 60));

    document.getElementById("urgency-message").innerHTML = "Only " + minutes + " minutes and " + seconds + " seconds left to get this exclusive offer!";

    if (timeLeft < 0) {
        clearInterval(countdown);
        document.getElementById("urgency-message").innerHTML = "Offer expired!";
    }

}, 1000 );

}

createUrgencyTimer();

```

This code creates a countdown timer that displays a message saying "Only X minutes and Y seconds left to get this exclusive offer!". By setting up the timer to expire website owners can urge visitors to take quick action. This technique can tap into their fear of missing out (FOMO). Remember to use this responsibly.
